--- title: Programming with SPSS type: docs editor_options: chunk_output_type: console --- The databases for SPSS can be downloaded [through this link](/files/data/SPSS/MATH80667A_SPSS_datasets.zip). # Videos There's a set of videos that walks through each section below. To make it easier for you to jump around the video examples, I cut the long video into smaller pieces and included them all in [one YouTube playlist](https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62). - [Loading data and two-sample t-test](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zZI2Oq1a2Og&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Pairwise contrasts](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AT6RsM6-EdU&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [One-way ANOVA](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7LLJWscsJrc&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [One-way ANOVA (website example)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dWKGp1khFeE&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Logical filters](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_So7PRQkHo4&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Contrasts and post-hoc comparisons](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jb2nftHBgsA&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Creating categorical variables with if-else statements](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8ba_EkcbIjw&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Two-way ANOVA](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7Z21rYuKMp0&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Two-way ANOVA (website example)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lxVJAzaBHyY&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [Three-way ANOVA (website example)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_imWUkEQVo8&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) - [ANCOVA (website example)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OuNr1en9i6Y&list=PLUB8VZzxA8Iv41lUAoTRNoat3oCVlFY62) You can also watch the playlist (and skip around to different sections) here:
